{
  "texts": [
    "The review highlighted the methodologies employed, including rule-based, neural network architectures and machine learning algorithms.",
    "Each approach exhibited its own strength and limitations in handling complexities of Indian languages.",
    "The paper offers a valuable insight for researchers, practitioners, and linguists aiming to enhance the accuracy and applicability of NER systems in the diverse linguistic landscape of India.In the future, we'll examine the knowledge gaps, problems, and challenges associated with deep learning-based for Named Entity Recognition in Indian languages.",
    "We'll also examine the techniques for NER in Indian languages and will go through their classification, advantages, and disadvantages.",
    "Further, we will focus on other entities such as Part-of-Speech and text summarization (TS) etc., and NER tagged corpus."
  ]
}